<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4039] Users should be able to choose custom TableInputFormats without modifying TableMapReduceUtil.initTableMapperJob().</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4039</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, org.apache.hadoop.hbase.mapreduce.TableMapReduceUtil.initTableMapperJob() forces any Hbase job to use the default TableInputFormat.class as the job&apos;s input format class.&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;job.setInputFormatClass(TableInputFormat.class);&quot; ==&amp;gt; This line is included in initTableMapperJob().&lt;br/&gt;
This restriction causes users to modify initTableMapperJob() in addition to implementing their own TableInputFormat. &lt;br/&gt;
It would be nicer if users can use custom TableInputFormats without additionally tampering with HBase source code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;HBase-0.90.3. OS, hardware specs not relevant.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
